<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="373" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,151,608]" pageId="22" pageNumber="373">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1451073566" country="China" county="Li" location="Li" municipality="The" pageId="22" pageNumber="373" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Fujian" typeStatus="holotype">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,367,392]" pageId="22" pageNumber="373">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was described from 
<collectingRegion box="[710,784,367,392]" country="China" name="Fujian" pageId="22" pageNumber="373">Fujian</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[799,866,367,392]" name="China" pageId="22" pageNumber="373">China</collectingCountry>
by 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:039582759E1B9F09FF5DF8AB16831951:8EE365B89E199F09FC5BFEC511E61AB9" box="[913,938,367,392]" country="China" county="Li" municipality="The" name="Li" pageId="22" pageNumber="373" stateProvince="Fujian">Li</location>
(1999) based on one male and one female specimen. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:039582759E1B9F09FF5DF8AB16831951:8EE365B89E199F09FEC5FE3E13EB1A9C" box="[271,423,404,429]" country="China" county="Li" municipality="The" name="Subsequently" pageId="22" pageNumber="373" stateProvince="Fujian">Subsequently</location>
, 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:039582759E1B9F09FF5DF8AB16831951:8EE365B89E199F09FE78FE3E10561A9C" box="[434,538,404,429]" country="China" county="Li" municipality="The" name="Kamitani" pageId="22" pageNumber="373" stateProvince="Fujian">Kamitani</location>
&amp; 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:039582759E1B9F09FF5DF8AB16831951:8EE365B89E199F09FDF5FE3E10D71A9C" box="[575,667,404,429]" country="China" county="Li" municipality="The" name="Hayashi" pageId="22" pageNumber="373" stateProvince="Fujian">Hayashi</location>
described 
<taxonomicName box="[789,968,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pristiophorus">
<emphasis box="[789,968,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="373">S. pristiophorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1037,1104,405,428]" name="Japan" pageId="22" pageNumber="373">Japan</collectingCountry>
. 
<collectingMunicipality box="[1115,1159,404,429]" pageId="22" pageNumber="373">The</collectingMunicipality>
illustrations given by 
<collectingCounty box="[1411,1436,404,429]" pageId="22" pageNumber="373">Li</collectingCounty>
are not very accurate. Dr. Jichun Xiang (personal communication) confirmed that the male genitalia illustrated here agree with the male genitalia of the 
<typeStatus box="[561,663,476,501]" pageId="22" pageNumber="373">holotype</typeStatus>
</materialsCitation>
. From examination of specimens from China and comparison of the original descriptions and illustrations of 
<taxonomicName box="[608,780,512,536]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pristophorus">
<emphasis box="[608,780,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="373">S. pristophorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it is clear that these two taxa are synonyms. This species can be distinguished by the serrate lateral margin of connective process near apex, aedeagal shaft with dorsal and ventral margin almost straight, apex with very small apically hooked processes at dorsal margin.
</paragraph>
